post_summaries.description: The image is a wide shot of a large, bronze-colored statue of a deity, likely a Buddha or bodhisattva, at the Kek Lok Si Temple in Penang, Malaysia. The statue is positioned outdoors, under a partially visible structure with ornate pillars and carvings. The sky is visible in the background. The statue is the focal point, and the surrounding architecture and natural elements provide context.

The image shows a woman posing in front of a street art mural in Penang, Malaysia. She is sitting on a bicycle and wearing colorful floral pants and a pink top. The mural depicts children riding a bicycle.

The image shows two women sitting at a table in a restaurant, enjoying vegan food in Kuala Lumpur. The post mentions that the food is "unusual" and "absurdly delicious." The hashtags #thehungrytapir, #lagula, #kusa, and #vegantravel are used.

The image shows two women standing in front of the Batu Caves in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. The background includes the colorful steps leading up to the caves and a large golden statue. The post's caption mentions the user traveled there by public transport, saw monkeys, and uses vegan-related hashtags.
Two women wearing purple head coverings and sunglasses are standing in front of a building in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia.

A woman is standing on a beach, holding a blue item above her head with both hands. She's wearing activewear including a pink shirt, patterned leggings, and blue sneakers. The background shows a windy beach with dunes.
